Interface IKandyCallService


  • public interface IKandyCallService

      • createVoipCall

        IKandyOutgoingCall createVoipCall(KandyRecord caller,
                                  KandyRecord callee,
                                  KandyOutgingVoipCallOptions outgoingVoipCallOptions)
        Create a VoIP call (IP to IP) object.

        Note:

        This interface only creates the call object: IKandyOutgoingCall

        In order to establish a call, use the method: createVoipCall

        Parameters:
        caller - The address defining the origin of the call (local party). optional, if you pass null default is the current user address.
        callee - address defining the target of the call (remote party)
        outgoingVoipCallOptions - is start sharing video in the outgoing call
        Returns:
        The outgoing call object

      • createPSTNCall

        IKandyOutgoingCall createPSTNCall(KandyRecord caller,
                                  String destination,
                                  KandyOutgoingPSTNCallOptions outgingPSTNCallOption)
        Create out call (IP to PSTN) object.

        Note The destination phone number must be E164 formatted number without the �+� prefix.

        Parameters:
        caller - The address defining the origin of the call (local party). optional, if you pass null the default is the current user address.
        destination - The destination phone number we want to call.
        outgingPSTNCallOption - is blocked id in PSTN call
        Returns:
        The outgoing call object

      • createSIPTrunkCall

        IKandyOutgoingCall createSIPTrunkCall(KandyRecord caller,
                                      KandyRecord callee)
        Using createSIPTrunkCall(KandyRecord, KandyRecord) requires a SIP trunk to be configured for your domain in Kandy.

        Note that when a SIP trunk is configured, the createPSTNCall(KandyRecord, String, KandyOutgoingPSTNCallOptions) command will be disabled

        Parameters:
        caller - The address defining the origin of the call (local party). optional, if you pass null default is the current user address.
        callee - address defining the target of the call (remote party)
        Returns:
        The outgoing call object

      • isInGSMCall

        boolean isInGSMCall()
        Returns:
